BLURSDAY stepped to the front from inside, showed the way to the far turn, vied with a trio of rivals on the far turn and into the lane, lost command in upper stretch, drifted in midstretch and weakened. AMERICAN CONQUEST was off slow and lost his path at the start, trailed on the inside into the lane, moved out but found traffic in upper stretch, altered in at the eighth pole but only found more traffic late and never could make a run. CANDY ON TOP stalked the pace on the inside, waited behind the leader on the far turn, remained inside to the stretch and never found room behind a weakening BLURSDAY. TAPIT ROCKS broke out a bit, started to pull and became rank into the first turn, continued to tug around the bend, settled inside on the backstretch, tipped out in the lane but lacked room and was forced to check hard late.
